The paper discusses the properties of radio channels in Massive MIMO, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also proposes a new measure to evaluate the quality of propagation, which is related to system optimization (cs.SY) and signal processing (cs.MM). Finally, the paper proposes a model to analyze the uniform random line-of-sight scenario, which is related to communication networks (cs.COM).
